Unit 2 of  Eskom's Duvha power station in Emalahleni (formerly Witbank) caught fire on Monday morning. According to Eskom spokesperson Sikonathi Mantshantsha, the unit had been offline for a general overhaul since January. The fire  was quickly extinguished. “Eskom is  investigating the  cause of the fire, and the extent of the damage and the possible return to service. No injuries to personnel were reported,” he said. TimesLIVE 